Are you an analytical Information & Technology (IT) whiz with a passion for spreadsheets and databases? The Ministry of Social Services’ Community Living Service Delivery (CLSD) branch is seeking a IT savvy Consultant to join our Program & Operational Supports (PrOS) team. Reporting to the Director of PrOS, the Consultant team provides quality assurance and program supports to CLSD’s provincial teams and partners. Our goal is simple: we strive to enhance CLSD funded services for individuals experiencing intellectual disabilities. A significant portion of this position will focus on the design, build, and maintenance of data management solutions supporting the tracking of licensing, incident reporting, and other information related to CLSD resources. This will include development and coordination of data migration strategies, drafting of policies and procedures to ensure data integrity, providing training to internal staff, and making overall recommendations related to data management and support.
As our ideal candidate, you will demonstrate your ability to:
Assess, recommend, and implement IT solutions to reach branch, program, and Ministry goals, organizational needs, and risks;
Build and maintain IT data management solutions;
Connect and analyze multiple data sets to improve evidence-based decision-making;
Rapidly learn various business areas and make recommendations on efficiencies through automation;
Streamline reporting functions;
Contribute to the development of policy and programs;
Apply a person centered lens to projects and services;
Communicate strategically, both orally and in writing, with internal and external stakeholders;
Negotiate and coordinate with partners to achieve results;
Create a culture of diversity and cross-team collaboration;
Play a leadership role in shaping the ethics and values of the organization by consistently communicating and exemplifying them;
Work autonomously, holding yourself and others accountable to achieve the results desired by the organization;
Champion innovation and lead organizational change;
Develop comprehensive plans that bridge complex issues and potentially span multiple fiscal years;
Foster a culture of continuous organizational improvement.

The successful candidate must be a team player, able to both lead and collaborate, with a reputation for integrity, and a focus on person-centered services and innovation. Previous experience working with quality control systems for human services, knowledge of data governance, and CLSD programs and services is an asset. Extensive experience with Microsoft Access and Excel required. Experience with SWIN and/or ArcGIS is also an asset. Typically, the knowledge, skills and abilities required to be successful in this position include a certificate/degree in data science, computer science, statistics or a social science with a strong emphasis on applied quantitative analyses. These educational qualifications should ideally be combined with at least three years of experience doing related work in a large organization. Applicants with strong quantitative backgrounds in public administration, data science, computer science or social sciences are likely to find this position rewarding.
A valid driver's licence is required as travel will be necessary.
Candidates must clearly indicate in their application, resume or cover letter how they have acquired the skills and abilities required for this position. Candidates will be screened based on the information provided.
What We Offer:
Meaningful work that positively impacts the individuals we serve;
A dynamic and challenging work for talented individuals;
Competitive salary;
Comprehensive benefits package including vacation, scheduled days off (SDOs), and pension;
An inclusive work environment with a strong commitment to workplace diversity.

We are committed to workplace diversity.
